header.gameNote: SAN JUAN SHOOTOUT AT SAN JUAN PR

article.headline: Northwestern 77, Utah 44
article.story: GUAYNABO, Puerto Rico (AP) -- Kevin Coble scored 22 points as Northwestern routed Utah 77-44 Thursday in the fifth place game of the San Juan Shootout. Coble was 8-for-11 from the field and hit all five 3-pointers for Northwestern (8-3), which scored 21 points off turnovers. Coble also led Northwestern with 23 points in a first-round loss Tuesday to Tennessee Tech, and scored 16 points in the Wildcats' victory over University of Puerto Rico-Mayaguez in the consolation round. Tim Doyle added 18 points and seven rebounds for Northwestern. The Wildcats shot 69 percent from the field and held the Utes to 40.9 percent. Shaun Green shot 6-for-9 from the field to finish with 14 points for Utah (5-7).
